The paper discusses linear-programming decoding algorithms and their pseudocodewords, which are commonly studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and coding theory (cs.DS) communities. The focus on graph-cover pseudocodewords suggests a connection to graph theory (cs.DM) and combinatorics (cs.CC).
